data.body:
**Operating system or device, Godot version, GPU Model and driver (if graphics related):**
Ubuntu 16.04.3, master branch 3f4062c

**Issue description:**
<!-- What happened, and what was expected. -->
it's from #11160.
I got compile error for building android template.

```
drivers/unix/dir_access_unix.cpp:209:15: error: use of undeclared identifier 'setmntent'
        FILE *mtab = setmntent("/etc/mtab", "r");
                     ^
drivers/unix/dir_access_unix.cpp:214:10: error: use of undeclared identifier 'getmntent_r'
                while (getmntent_r(mtab, &mnt, strings, sizeof(strings))) {
                       ^
drivers/unix/dir_access_unix.cpp:223:3: error: use of undeclared identifier 'endmntent'; did you mean 'getmntent'?
                endmntent(mtab);
                ^~~~~~~~~
                getmntent
/mnt/2TB/Development/NVPACK/android-ndk-r15c-linux/platforms/android-18/arch-arm/usr/include/mntent.h:49:16: note: 
      'getmntent' declared here
struct mntent* getmntent(FILE*);
               ^
3 errors generated.
scons: *** [drivers/unix/dir_access_unix.android.opt.armv7.neon.o] Error 1
```

this is what `/android-ndk-r15c-linux/platforms/android-18/arch-arm/usr/include/mntent.h` has inside
```cpp
#ifndef _MNTENT_H_
#define _MNTENT_H_

#include <stdio.h>

#define MNTTYPE_IGNORE "ignore"

struct mntent
{
    char* mnt_fsname;
    char* mnt_dir;
    char* mnt_type;
    char* mnt_opts;
    int mnt_freq;
    int mnt_passno;
};

__BEGIN_DECLS
struct mntent* getmntent(FILE*);
__END_DECLS

#endif
```

I found `/android-ndk-r15c-linux/platforms/android-21/arch-arm/usr/include/mntent.h` has those functions.
```cpp
int endmntent(FILE*);
struct mntent* getmntent(FILE*);
struct mntent* getmntent_r(FILE*, struct mntent*, char*, int);
FILE* setmntent(const char*, const char*);
```

**Steps to reproduce:**
`scons platform=android tools=no`

